This paper deals with the problem of classification using Gaussian processes and proposes a new approach for training inducing input GP models. This work is primarily focused on machine learning and optimization, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with classification and dimensionality reduction, which are common topics in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of Gaussian processes for classification also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the proposed method, which is a common topic in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new approach for optimization, which is a common topic in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
